%pyspark
from pyspark.sql.functions import *
from pyspark.sql.types import IntegerType
from pyspark.sql.types import TimestampType
from pyspark.ml.feature import StringIndexer
from pyspark.sql.functions import regexp_replace, substring, length, col, expr
from pyspark.sql import functions as sf
from pyspark.sql.types import IntegerType



data = spark.read.csv('/user/zeppelin/dataset/flight_delays_train.csv',inferSchema='true',header='true',sep=',')



data = data.withColumnRenamed("UniqueCarrier Code","UniqueCarrierCode")
data = data.withColumnRenamed("Origin Code","OriginCode")
data = data.withColumnRenamed("Dest Code","DestCode")
data = data.withColumnRenamed("dep_delayed_15min","label")

data = data.withColumn('Month', regexp_replace('Month', 'c-', ''))
data = data.withColumn('DayofMonth', regexp_replace('DayofMonth', 'c-', ''))
data = data.withColumn('DayOfWeek', regexp_replace('DayOfWeek', 'c-', ''))

data = data.withColumn('label', regexp_replace('label', 'N', '0'))
data = data.withColumn('label', regexp_replace('label', 'Y', '1'))

data = data.withColumn('DepTime', sf.concat(sf.lit('00'), col('DepTime')))
data = data.withColumn("DepTime",expr("substring(DepTime, 1, length(DepTime)-2)"))

data = data.withColumn("DepTime", data["DepTime"].cast(IntegerType()))
data = data.withColumn("Month", data["Month"].cast(IntegerType()))
data = data.withColumn("DayofMonth", data["DayofMonth"].cast(IntegerType()))
data = data.withColumn("DayOfWeek", data["DayOfWeek"].cast(IntegerType()))
data = data.withColumn("label", data["label"].cast(IntegerType()))


spark.sql("DROP TABLE IF EXISTS FlightDelay")
data.write.saveAsTable("FlightDelay")

data.printSchema()
